820
00:58:51,870 --> 00:58:53,470
Dad!

821
00:59:05,240 --> 00:59:06,300
Honey.

822
00:59:07,240 --> 00:59:08,600
What? What is it now?

823
00:59:09,240 --> 00:59:13,780
Could you take this home for me?

824
00:59:13,780 --> 00:59:15,970
I'm working here. Do you want to die?

825
00:59:16,440 --> 00:59:19,840
I think the baby...

826
00:59:20,700 --> 00:59:21,700
So...

827
00:59:22,570 --> 00:59:23,640
I have to go to the hospital.

828
00:59:25,540 --> 00:59:28,440
They said it's a boy this time.

829
00:59:28,440 --> 00:59:30,740
Don't make a fuss. Why would there be anything wrong?

830
00:59:31,900 --> 00:59:32,900
Just go home!

831
00:59:39,040 --> 00:59:42,340
Both the mum and the daughter are driving me crazy.

832
01:00:11,670 --> 01:00:14,120
You came to ruin our family, didn't you?

833
01:00:14,120 --> 01:00:16,420
Where did my clothes go after you washed them?

834
01:00:16,420 --> 01:00:20,180
You threw it out because you knew I liked it, didn't you?

835
01:00:20,180 --> 01:00:21,740
Well? Get up.

836
01:00:23,400 --> 01:00:26,970
Mother, please! I'm so sorry!

837
01:00:27,500 --> 01:00:29,300
Please don't pull my hair!

838
01:00:29,700 --> 01:00:32,440
Where is it? Go find it!

839
01:00:32,440 --> 01:00:34,070
You threw it out, right?

840
01:01:07,940 --> 01:01:11,320
It's just a cold. Why would she call her mum about that?

841
01:01:11,320 --> 01:01:13,600
What did you teach your kids?

842
01:01:14,140 --> 01:01:16,670
They're such whiners. They take after you, you know that?

843
01:01:17,200 --> 01:01:18,290
What is this?

844
01:01:18,290 --> 01:01:20,600
It's such a waste to throw it out.

845
01:01:20,600 --> 01:01:23,700
Then why did you pay money to buy it then make it go bad?

846
01:01:23,700 --> 01:01:26,070
You are well out of your mind, aren't you?

847
01:01:26,070 --> 01:01:28,070
If anyone saw you eat your three meals for a day,

848
01:01:28,070 --> 01:01:30,000
they'd think you're a wrestler.

849
01:01:30,000 --> 01:01:31,700
A fat wrestler at that!

850
01:01:31,700 --> 01:01:32,700
Stay here for 10 more minutes.

851
01:01:35,640 --> 01:01:37,000
What about the world tour you promised me...

852
01:01:37,000 --> 01:01:40,040
when I took care of your eight siblings?

853
01:01:40,040 --> 01:01:42,670
If I didn't hold you back with that promise,

854
01:01:42,670 --> 01:01:44,070
you would've left me already.

855
01:01:44,940 --> 01:01:47,650
I don't want to die in a hospital...

856
01:01:47,650 --> 01:01:49,200
like my mum did.

857
01:01:49,570 --> 01:01:51,700
I want to fly free like a bird...

858
01:01:52,470 --> 01:01:54,740
and die on the streets.

859
01:02:01,070 --> 01:02:02,140
Mum...

860
01:04:16,900 --> 01:04:17,900
Okay.

861
01:04:18,500 --> 01:04:20,870
If you won't come over, I'll go.

862
01:04:21,240 --> 01:04:22,380
Where do you live?

863
01:04:22,380 --> 01:04:23,930
Shall I ask your mum?

864
01:04:23,930 --> 01:04:26,400
Just tell him to come over.

865
01:04:26,400 --> 01:04:28,590
He wants to give you something to write about.

866
01:04:28,590 --> 01:04:30,170
Just spare him an hour.

867
01:04:31,440 --> 01:04:32,920
And get rid of this.

868
01:04:32,920 --> 01:04:34,170
You guys broke up.

869
01:04:34,170 --> 01:04:35,200
Be quiet.

870
01:04:38,240 --> 01:04:42,270
I only have an hour. Will that be enough?

871
01:04:43,670 --> 01:04:44,670
Okay.

872
01:04:45,900 --> 01:04:48,190
I know where you live. I dropped Jeong A off before.

873
01:04:48,190 --> 01:04:50,130
It's block 409, flat 505.

874
01:04:50,130 --> 01:04:51,450
Do you know where?

875
01:04:51,450 --> 01:04:52,940
I'll come over.

876
01:04:58,640 --> 01:05:00,270
He's so annoying.

877
01:05:00,940 --> 01:05:04,760
Don't be like that to the old man. You're such a brat.

878
01:05:04,760 --> 01:05:07,140
He should be more thoughtful.

879
01:05:07,140 --> 01:05:09,750
He acts like old age makes him special.

880
01:05:09,750 --> 01:05:11,400
By the time I'm done with the book,

881
01:05:11,400 --> 01:05:13,200
I think I'll hate talking to old people.

882
01:05:14,870 --> 01:05:18,140
They act how they want just because they think they'll die soon.

883
01:05:18,480 --> 01:05:20,390
It's obvious what he'll say.

884
01:05:20,390 --> 01:05:22,610
He'll either brag or complain about his life.

885
01:05:23,130 --> 01:05:24,130
Or he'll curse others.

886
01:05:24,600 --> 01:05:27,740
I have a feeling you're talking about me.

887
01:05:34,600 --> 01:05:35,600
What was that?

888
01:05:38,370 --> 01:05:40,700
I started exercising my legs at the pool.

889
01:05:45,300 --> 01:05:46,300
It's you.

890
01:05:47,850 --> 01:05:48,930
How are you?

891
01:05:48,930 --> 01:05:51,250
Wan's not in. She just left.

892
01:05:51,250 --> 01:05:53,040
Oh, that's fine.

893
01:05:53,040 --> 01:05:54,140
I can talk to you.

894
01:05:54,570 --> 01:05:55,570
Are you well?

895
01:05:56,640 --> 01:05:59,400
My brother can walk now.

896
01:06:00,170 --> 01:06:01,400
You can't, can you?

897
01:06:03,270 --> 01:06:04,840
It was a serious accident.

898
01:06:06,070 --> 01:06:07,370
I see.

899
01:06:07,770 --> 01:06:10,700
You still have to exercise your legs.

900
01:06:11,140 --> 01:06:13,540
I bet they hurt a lot at night.

901
01:06:14,070 --> 01:06:15,400
Take care.

902
01:06:16,770 --> 01:06:18,240
And date women.

903
01:06:22,500 --> 01:06:24,770
How's your mother? I heard she's ill.

904
01:06:25,300 --> 01:06:26,740
I'm going to take her to the doctor.

905
01:06:27,370 --> 01:06:28,680
Let's talk again.

906
01:06:28,680 --> 01:06:29,710
I have to go.

907
01:07:30,040 --> 01:07:31,970
She said, "My stomach feels strange."

908
01:07:34,470 --> 01:07:37,900
She was carrying groceries on her head.

909
01:07:38,900 --> 01:07:40,340
But I just got mad.

910
01:07:43,140 --> 01:07:45,070
Blood was dripping down her legs.

911
01:07:45,970 --> 01:07:46,970
So...

912
01:07:47,770 --> 01:07:50,040
she stayed at a hospital for two days.

913
01:07:51,470 --> 01:07:52,970
I felt bad for her.

914
01:07:54,500 --> 01:07:55,540
After that,

915
01:07:56,070 --> 01:07:58,210
I should have kept my mouth shut.

916
01:07:59,240 --> 01:08:01,400
But I said, "Get up and cook for me."

917
01:08:02,370 --> 01:08:03,370
I said that.

918
01:08:07,840 --> 01:08:09,370
After that,

919
01:08:09,900 --> 01:08:12,800
we both acted like nothing happened.

920
01:08:17,840 --> 01:08:18,870
We were together.

921
01:08:19,840 --> 01:08:20,900
But now, I'm alone.

922
01:08:24,600 --> 01:08:27,070
Others, and even Soon Young,

923
01:08:28,340 --> 01:08:30,280
think that I was mean and arrogant...

924
01:08:30,280 --> 01:08:33,870
even though I knew I was wrong.

925
01:08:33,870 --> 01:08:34,870
But I had no idea.

926
01:08:35,870 --> 01:08:37,070
It was so long ago...

927
01:08:37,840 --> 01:08:40,300
and my focus was on making a living.

928
01:08:44,500 --> 01:08:46,440
I did so terribly wrong, didn't I?

929
01:08:49,140 --> 01:08:50,990
The biggest sin...

930
01:08:50,990 --> 01:08:53,670
is not knowing what you did wrong. Being ignorant.

931
01:08:55,770 --> 01:08:58,640
You can't count the mistakes you didn't know you made.

932
01:09:04,040 --> 01:09:05,040
That's why...

933
01:09:06,770 --> 01:09:09,710
I will let my wife go.

934
01:09:13,300 --> 01:09:15,300
You can write about everything I said...

935
01:09:16,170 --> 01:09:19,000
if you want others to know there are people like me.

936
01:09:20,710 --> 01:09:21,710
Well...

937
01:09:22,470 --> 01:09:23,470
Seok Gyun.

938
01:09:24,800 --> 01:09:27,980
Just like how you talked to me so freely just now,

939
01:09:27,980 --> 01:09:29,190
tell Jeong A...

940
01:09:29,190 --> 01:09:31,600
I can't cook or do the washing.

941
01:09:33,800 --> 01:09:34,800
No.

942
01:09:36,710 --> 01:09:38,140
I won't work her any more.

943
01:09:39,070 --> 01:09:40,070
Go.

944
01:09:43,570 --> 01:09:45,040
And quit smoking, Kid.

945
01:09:49,870 --> 01:09:52,000
You should eat lunch.

946
01:09:53,970 --> 01:09:55,500
Shall I cook something?

947
01:09:58,710 --> 01:09:59,710
Seok Gyun.

948
01:10:07,570 --> 01:10:08,570
Seok Gyun.

949
01:10:10,470 --> 01:10:12,400
Just go.

950
01:10:17,570 --> 01:10:18,570
Okay, then.

951
01:10:30,170 --> 01:10:31,340
Someone said that...

952
01:10:32,340 --> 01:10:34,980
we do more bad than good...

953
01:10:34,980 --> 01:10:37,210
during our whole lives.

954
01:10:37,840 --> 01:10:38,980
That's why...

955
01:10:38,980 --> 01:10:41,930
we have much more to gain than to lose,

956
01:10:41,930 --> 01:10:43,370
and we are blessed.

957
01:10:45,170 --> 01:10:47,340
So instead of having regrets,

958
01:10:47,340 --> 01:10:49,570
we should be grateful we're alive.

959
01:10:54,600 --> 01:10:56,650
Is life really a blessing we should be...

960
01:10:56,650 --> 01:10:57,740
grateful for?

961
01:10:58,870 --> 01:11:01,540
Even to my mum and grandma?

962
01:11:03,000 --> 01:11:05,670
I sincerely hope that this will be...

963
01:11:05,670 --> 01:11:08,830
the ending to the book that I'll leave to my mother when I go...

964
01:11:08,830 --> 01:11:10,070
live with Yeon Ha.

965
01:11:14,000 --> 01:11:15,600
Ms Jang Nan Hee is...

966
01:11:15,600 --> 01:11:16,620
That's me.

967
01:12:05,900 --> 01:12:08,000
(Dear My Friends)

968
01:12:08,000 --> 01:12:10,330
"The husband must speak in a small voice..."

969
01:12:10,330 --> 01:12:12,540
"and always be kind." What a joke.

970
01:12:12,860 --> 01:12:14,740
I pressed the button.

971
01:12:14,740 --> 01:12:16,270
At least, he won't starve.

972
01:12:16,270 --> 01:12:18,220
Do you like me or him?

973
01:12:18,600 --> 01:12:19,620
Did you sleep with him?

974
01:12:19,620 --> 01:12:20,780
What?

975
01:12:20,780 --> 01:12:22,260
Don't fall for anyone else.

976
01:12:22,260 --> 01:12:24,720
You sound like an evil boyfriend...

977
01:12:24,720 --> 01:12:25,860
who sells your girlfriend.

978
01:12:25,860 --> 01:12:27,200
I'll be waiting.

979
01:12:27,200 --> 01:12:30,030
I should tell Hee Ja's kids, right?

980
01:12:30,510 --> 01:12:31,610
She's not at church?

981
01:12:32,330 --> 01:12:34,000
How are we going to find her?

